## Variant-Based Styling Pattern

Use objects to organize variant styles:

```typescript
const variantStyles = {
  default: {
    container: 'aucctus-bg-secondary aucctus-border-secondary',
    icon: 'aucctus-stroke-brand-primary',
    text: 'aucctus-text-brand-primary',
  },
  success: {
    container: 'aucctus-bg-success-secondary aucctus-border-success',
    icon: 'aucctus-stroke-success-primary',
    text: 'aucctus-text-success-primary',
  },
  error: {
    container: 'aucctus-bg-error-secondary aucctus-border-error',
    icon: 'aucctus-stroke-error-primary',
    text: 'aucctus-text-error-primary',
  },
};

const styles = variantStyles[variant];

<div className={cn('rounded-lg border p-4', styles.container)}>
  <Icon variant='icon-name' className={cn('h-5 w-5', styles.icon)} />
  <span className={cn('aucctus-text-sm-semibold', styles.text)}>
    Text
  </span>
</div>
```

---

## Important Notes

### Hover Classes
❌ **WRONG**: `hover:aucctus-bg-primary-hover`
✅ **CORRECT**: `aucctus-bg-primary-hover`

Classes with `-hover` suffix already include base styling and hover behavior.

### Icon Usage
```typescript
import { Icon } from '@components';

<Icon 
  variant='clipboard' 
  className='h-5 w-5 aucctus-stroke-brand-primary' 
/>
```

